10.categories: Mobile, Navigation, Public Safety, Security

12.short_description: CityHeroes, a web and mobile app, enables individuals to collaboratively report and solve collective issues and threatening situations.

18.description:
CityHeroes is an application for smartphones that enables people to send a report about a particular situation in less than 30 seconds. Either it be a loose wire at the office or a terrorist treat at a public event, the information of such event may help save lives. CityHeroes also provides a web platform where the companies, governments, and organizations can manage the reports in real-time, obtain the exact location of the problem, forward the information to the approrpiate institutions, and ideally find a solution to the problem. In this same form CityHeroes can send alerts to the members of an organization when a particular situation requires rapid and effective communication.

CityHeroes is also connected to LifeTag, a series of electronic devices that can be either carried around by people or be installed in buses, homes, and other locations. These devices are independent of the cell-phones and are capable of generating information and immediate alerts in case of critical situations. These devices are connected to the CityHeroes system in order to shorten the response times and enable the institutions to take action in the shortest amount of time possible.

12.short_description: MITA invests in globally-scalable startups, principally from Mexico or LatAm founder teams, based on strong core enabling technologies.

18.description: We invest in globally-scalable startups, principally from Mexico or LatAm founder teams, based on strong core enabling technologies (with an AI and Blockchain focus). We anticipate the most promising opportunities utilizing these enabling technologies being in FinTech, EdTech, IoT, IIoT, SaaS, and E-Commerce verticals. Our investments stages will range from Seed and Series A companies coming out of Mexico to Series B companies from other countries wanting to expand into Mexico/LatAm. Portfolio construction (dollar allocation) will be 20% Seed, 30% Growth, and 50% Expansion. Our strategy includes active engagement with founders, clear deployment plans and criteria for follow-on investments, early planning to attract future co-investors, and an identified path for exit.
